  "prompt": "Which is a suitable inpatient drug and alcohol rehab center near Warren County IL?",
  "response": "Finding the right inpatient drug and alcohol rehabilitation center is a crucial step toward recovery. Near Warren County, Illinois, there are several reputable facilities that offer comprehensive treatment programs. Below are some options you might consider:\n\n### 1. **Aurora Behavioral Health Hospital**\n- **Location:** Aurora, IL\n- **Services:** Offers inpatient treatment for substance use disorders, including detoxification, therapy, and aftercare planning.\n- **Contact:** (630) 798-5600\n- **Website:** [Aurora Behavioral Health](https://www.aurorabehavioralhealth.org/)\n\n### 2. **MacLean Hospital**\n- **Location:** Mendota, IL\n- **Services:** Provides specialized programs for addiction treatment, including residential care, counseling, and relapse prevention.\n- **Contact:** (815) 459-5311\n- **Website:** [MacLean Hospital](https://www.macleanhospital.org/)\n\n### 3. **Rosbank Behavioral Healthcare**\n- **Location:** Peoria, IL\n- **Services:** Offers a range of services including inpatient rehabilitation, outpatient programs, and mental health services integrated with addiction treatment.\n- **Contact:** (309) 795-2000\n- **Website:** [Rosbank Behavioral Healthcare](https://www.rosbankhealth.com/)\n\n### 4. **Recovery Place of Peoria**\n- **Location:** Peoria, IL\n- **Services:** Provides inpatient and outpatient addiction treatment programs, including individual and group therapy, educational sessions, and support services.\n- **Contact:** (309) 460-1111\n- **Website:** [Recovery Place of Peoria](https://recoveryplaceofpeoria.com/)\n\n### Additional Resources:\n- **SAMHSA Treatment Locator:** The Substance Abuse and Mental Health Services Administration offers a [treatment locator](https://findtreatment.samhsa.gov/) tool that can help you find nearby facilities based on your specific needs.\n- **Local Healthcare Providers:** Consulting with a healthcare professional or contacting local hospitals can provide personalized recommendations and referrals.\n\n### Important Considerations:\n- **Accreditation:** Ensure the facility is accredited by relevant authorities (e.g., CARF, JCAHO) to guarantee quality care.\n- **Insurance and Costs:** Verify that the center accepts your insurance or inquire about payment options and financial assistance.\n- **Specialized Programs:** Depending on specific needs (e.g., dual diagnosis, age-specific programs), look for centers that offer tailored treatments.\n\n### Disclaimer:\nWhile I strive to provide accurate and up-to-date information, it's essential to verify details directly with the facility and consult with a healthcare professional to determine the best treatment option for your situation.",
